 <song> 
<title>367 MOUNT EPHRAIM</title>
<lyrics>[V1]
 367 MOUNT EPHRAIM
 REVIVE Thy work, O Lord,
 Thy mighty arm make bare.
 Speak with the voice which wakes the dead ; 
 First make Thy people hear.
[V2]
 Revive Thy work, O Lord,
 Disturb this sleep of death.
 Quicken the smouldering embers, 
 Lord, By Thine almighty breath.
[V3]
 Revive Thy work, O Lord,
 Create soul-thirst for Thee.
 And hungering for the bread of life, 
 Oh, may our spirits be!
[V4]
 Revive Thy work, O Lord, 
 Exalt Thy precious name.
 And by the Spirit, Lord, our love 
 For Thee and Thine inflame.
[V5]
 Revive Thy work, O Lord, 
 Give power unto Thy word;
 Grant that Thy blessed gospel may
 In living faith be heard.
[V6]
 Revive Thy work, O Lord,
 And give refreshing showers.
 The glory, Lord, shall be Thine own,
 The blessing shall be ours. Amen. 
</lyrics>
